div.p: A economic waveform is the current state of a combination of assets that will experience a state change that can be realized as a ratification of that state change between the assets involved prior to ratification of that state change modeled to represent the potential valid state changes.

An econocmic waveform collapses upon ratification of a potential state change. When a economic waveform is modeled it represents the base state upon initiation of a state change from which potential state will be realized based on user interaction.

In some cases, virtual tokens will have to included in the model to represent the potential for various state changes. A token counts as virtual is there is not feasible method to collapse the waveform being modeled in such a way to effect a state change that would result in a token with the properties of the virtual token required for a complete model of the eeconomic potential of a given starting state and the actions a user can tke to ratify a state change.

Economic waveforms are relative from the perspective of a pottential economic actor. While it would be possible to model a economic waveform from the perspective of a platform, this would only be a virtual waveform as the platform can not be a economic actor as it can not initiate a transaction.

A translation must often incorporate virtual tokens to define routes and sources of economic energy nessecary to model a translation.
